Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje of Kano State has called on Imams of Jumu’at Mosques to offer special prayers for a peaceful and seamless transition and handover of power to the incoming administration in the state. Already, Ganduje has directed political appointees in the state to step down from office on or before midnight on Friday. On Wednesday, the Secretary to the Kano state government, SSG, Alhaji Usman Alhaji on behalf of the outgoing governor handed over the transition report to the Representatives of the incoming NNPP administration in Kano state. The state commissioner for Information and Internal Affairs, Malam Muhammad Garba said in a statement Friday morning that, while the Ganduje administration has entrenched policies that guarantee peace in the last eight years, there was the need for it’s consolidation through fervent prayers. He also commended the entire people of the state for their support to the administration which enables the execution of laudable development programmes.